   Request for Applications (RFAs)

   There are currently no RFA's; however, please check this site for
   future postings. Details on other grants and RFA's can be found on the
   NIH Grants and Contracts Page.

   Additional information links for RFA Applicants:
     * Investigator's Handbook (frames version)
     * Investigator's Handbook (no frames)
     * Letter of Intent (LOI) Submission Form and Guidelines
     * CDUS Instructions

   Details on grants can be found on the NIH Grants and Contracts

                                    [Top]
     __________________________________________________________________

   Program Announcements (PAs)

   There are currently two PAs sponsored by CTEP. The title and PA number
   are provided here for your convenience. Details on these and other
   grants can be found on the NIH Grants and Contracts Page.

   Title: "Exploratory Grants for Correlative Laboratory Studies and
   Clinical Trials"

   PA Number: PA-98-042

   NIH Guide: Vol. 25, No. 12, 3/20/98

   Application Receipt Dates: June 1, October 1, February 1
   Title: "Small Grants for Therapeutic Clinical Trials of Malignancies"

   PA Number: PAR-97-006

   NIH Guide: Vol. 25, No. 37, 11/1/96

   Application Receipt Dates: May 15, September 15, January 15

   Four additional Program Announcements sponsored by the National Cancer
   Institute are also relevant to clinical oncologists:

   Title: "Management of Symptoms Secondary to Treatment"

   PA Number: PA 97-082

   NIH Guide: Vol. 26, No. 24, 7/25/97

   Application Receipt Dates: February 1, June 1, October 1
   Title: "Exploratory Studies in Cancer Diagnostics"

   PA Number: PA-98-022

   NIH Guide: January 16, 1998

   Application Receipt Dates: February 1, June 1, October 1


   Title: "Exploratory/Developmental Grants for Diagnostic Cancer Imaging"

   PA Number: PA-98-008

   NIH Guide, Volume 26, Number 37, November 7, 1997

   Application Receipt Dates: February 1, June 1, October 1

